Fans of romantic drama certainly had a field day on Wednesday, December 29 when Inkblot Productions released its latest cinematic project titled ‘Superstar’. ‘Superstar’, which stars in the lead, Nancy Isime follows the rise to stardom of an up-and-coming actress Queen, as she ploughs through life and love in 21st century Nollywood. She must find the balance between artistry and stardom, whilst surviving the demons of her past. Asides Isime, we see other familiar Nollywood faces like Timini Egbuson, Deyemi Okanlawon, Ufuoma Mcdermott, Daniel Etim-Effiong, Eku Edewor, Teniola Aladese, Lord Frank and more. Uke Kingdom Crowns Actress Tayo Sobola Queen Mother Sola Sobowale Celebrates At 58 The movie is directed by one of Nigeria’s fast-rising directors, Akhigbe Ilozobhie popularly known as Akay Mason, who wrote the script alongside Uyoyou Adia and Inkblot, co-founder Chinaza Onuzo. Akay Mason, who also directed the award-winning film, Elevator Baby said, “making this movie has been a dream come true, a chance to tell a story that has been dear to my heart for so long. It promises to be a cinematic experience like no other.” On the movie and Akay’s growth as a director, co-founder Inkblot, Zulumoke Oyibo said, “We first employed Akay as a Production Assistant in 2015, and we are so proud to see his growth and how he continues to break new ground in his writing and directing career. ‘Superstar’ is a testament to his vision and talent. The audience is in for an exciting ride this December.”